\f0\b\fs26 \cf0 Region Five - Fungus Caves (35-46)
\f1\b0\fs24 \

\f0\fs26 The Fungus caves are actually collapsed sections of the dungeon where an overhead river burrowed down and made the area unstable, causing cave-ins. The system of cave-like chambers are ruled by The Mushroom King, a canny Fungal leader, who defends his spores with a strange and alien intelligence. He has a deal with the goblins, who provide rotting logs in return for magic mushrooms and Shrieker spores. He has his people lay out rotting meat along a path to draw the spawn of the Slimelord out into the wider dungeon and away from the fungal caves. He also pacifies various giant insects using one of his many spore clouds. These insects effectively ignore the Fungi now and act as unwitting guards. 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\b\fs26 \cf0 Running the Fungi people
\f1\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\fs26 \cf0 The Mushroom King seeks to protect his flock and works both untiringly and cleverly to cancel or destroy creatures who might threaten the myconids. The Mushroom King will most likely want to parley with the adventurers before combat. He is psychic, using telepathy to talk in any language. The King is allied with the goblin Reaping Madkin, who he has manipulated into providing him with a great deal of information about the 1st level of the dungeon. He too is concerned about the Pig-Faced orcs and will aid the adventurers against them, possibly by supplying them with poisons and potions, but mostly with advice and information. He will certainly act as a go-between if the party want to talk to the goblins. He is tricky though and will see the party as danger to the long term balance of the level and if they deal with the orcs happily send them through the one way teleport into the Tomb Of Judder, without telling them that so far it\'92s been a one way trip. The King himself is highly intelligent but also quite alien. He\'92ll constantly describe to whoever he is communicating their features and mannerism for example, and if he stands still for more than a minute the ground around him will start to erupt in small mushrooms of various types. \'a0
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs26  
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\b\fs26 Helpful
\f1\b0\fs24 \

\f0\fs26 If the characters can convince the King that they mean no harm to his flock he may aid the party against particular foes. He worries a great deal about the Orcs and is also concerned about whatever haunts the crawling warrens. He has an alliance with the Beetle Herder and may travel with the party to parlay with her to gain access to the Tomb Of The Judder. The King distrusts mammal life forms, and so the party will need to make offerings and placations towards him at first. Madkin the goblin shaman might be useful here, if the party has been deemed the tribes saviours. The King also knows that the secret to opening the door to the obelisk on this level involves find the keys, of which he has one. \'a0
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\b\fs26 Harmful
\f1\b0\fs24 \

\f0\fs26 If the party attack the fungus folk without provocation the King will declare war on them. He may send myconids out to lure them into fighting the Owlbear or the undead. He also knows the secret to a spore spray that attracts slimes and molds, which maybe his revenge if they party confront him directly.
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\b\fs26 Disdainful
\f1\b0\fs24 \

\f0\fs26 This is the Kings default position, he\'92ll attempt to drive away the party without direct combat, if he considers them powerful, he may well attempt to bribe them or offer useful information that leads them away from his domain.\'a0
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\b\fs26 \cf0 35. Slimey entrance way : mushrooms, collapse
\f1\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\i\fs26 \cf0 As you move down the corridor you notice a slight breeze that brings with it damp air and an earthy smell, tinged with a putrid taint. Little by little you notice the cold stone ways of hall become encrusted with lichen, mold and even fungus. You seem to be approaching an open doorway ahead and it seems mud and earth spill from it.\'a0
\f1\i0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\i\fs26 \cf0 In the chamber beyond, the walls and ceiling have partially collapsed, becoming much more uneven and rough, further into the ruined dungeon the fungus and mold becomes much more prevalent and the previous rectangular nature of the dungeon gives way to an almost cave like feel. Ahead natural light sparsely filters in from high up above. 
\f1\i0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\b\fs26 \cf0 36. Rotting meat : rotting meat, stench
\f1\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\i\fs26 \cf0 The reek of rotting meat assaults your senses, and you spot carcasses littering the floor, lined up along the eastern wall. The animals seem to be various forest creatures, although there are some bones that indicate more intelligent creatures have lain here as well. 
\f1\i0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\fs26 \cf0 Pieces of rotting meat are used by the Mushroom king to lure the spawn of Jubliex from area 37 towards the main dungeon and away from his flock.
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\b\fs26 \cf0 37. Spawning ground Of The Slimelord : decay, sphincter altar, oozes, treasure
\f1\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\i\fs26 \cf0 Filth and slime have completely overtaken the tumbled walls of the dungeon in this area, the smell of mould is overpowering and even the air feels rotten. Slime covered pools of stagnant water and litter the floor particularly around a large and disturbing block of what appears to be soap stone in the centre of the room. It has been carved into the shape of some kind of sphincter like that of a huge slug or sea beast and drips with slime. A dull keening surrounds you, seemingly without source. Glints of metal catches the light from your torches further into the cave. The glistening very walls seem to be moving.
\f1\i0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\fs26 \cf0 Jubliex the Slimelord once had a hidden shrine in this chamber and was worshipped by a long vanished gang of mutant Kobolds. Now only the horrible sphincter shaped soapstone altar remains, which occasionally spews forth an ooze, slime, jelly or mould. Currently two Green Slime, a Grey Ooze, a Gelatinous Cube all reside in here and would be extremely dangerous should the players stumble in, as the are all hard to spot - DC15 perception check. Their acids have failed to dissolve a suit of +1 chainmail, 230 g.p. and 3 rubies worth 100 g.p. each. Finally an Obelisk key can be found amongst the filth.\'a0Players, especially druids, might seek to destroy the altar and will need strong magic to do so. If they are successful they will be cursed by Jubilex, but receive favour from other nature aligned gods and patrons. The Fungal Folk will surprisingly not be entirely grateful either as their region is avoided because of it\'92s association with oozes. \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\b\fs26 \cf0 38. Shriekers! : shriekers, light, a way up. 
\f1\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\i\fs26 \cf0 More light comes in from the broken ceiling here, illuminating a large cave-like chamber that\'92s filled with debris and soil from above. Numerous small plants try and get a foot hold in rays of sunlight but the majority of the room is over run by mushrooms both huge and small, arrayed in a variety of colours. 
\f1\i0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\fs26 \cf0 Unless the characters entering this area are silent or invisibly read the following also. 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\i\fs26 \cf0 As you step closer, howling gaseous shrieks start up from large purple mushrooms that line the walls, no doubt alerting anything nearby to your presence. 
\f1\i0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\fs26 \cf0 There are 4 shrieker mushrooms here that rely on vibrations and changes in light to detect intruders. 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\fs26 \cf0 If the characters manage to enter the mushroom kingdom without detection they\'92ll take the Fungus people by surprise at first and the DM should adjust their reaction accordingly. Characters can climb up and out of the dungeon if they have rope and grappling hook. If they do, they find themselves in a dense wood at the top of the plateau the dungeon buries into. Finding a way down to the trail back to the city of Corsent adds an extra day to the journey but provides a more secretive rout into the dungeon, if the Fungal people are dealt with, one way \'a0or another. 
\f1\fs24 \
