\f0\b\fs26 \cf0 45. Cave Of The Beetle Herder : Banshaer, beetles, potions
\f1\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\i\fs26 \cf0 Yet more debris litters this chamber, although what appears to be a circular tent dominates your view. All around scuttle more insects and the floor seems almost to be moving. The tent is made from wooden branches and covered in mouldy cloth. \'a0\'a0
\f1\i0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\fs26 \cf0 A moody Banshaer hermit tends her flock of giant beetles and brews strange concoctions in her tent to sell in the deep market. The beetles are unlikely to attack unless provoked as the hermit keeps them well fed, however she will react using her druidic magic if the players act aggressively, with the beetles rushing to defend her. She makes and keeps numerous potions (2 healing, one each of resistance to fire, lightning and cold, 2 potions of neutralise poison, 2 fire breathing potions). The Banshaer keeps hidden beneath loose rocks 280 g.p.\
\
Banshaer, 4 fire beetles
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs26 \uc0\u8232 
\b Running the Beetle Herder
\f1\b0\fs24 \

\f0\b\fs26 Helpful
\f1\b0\fs24 \

\f0\fs26 The Beetle Herder knows that the throne teleports those who sit on it away and has never seen anyone come back. She might offer this information to the characters. She might also offer the party potions, in return for promises about not attacking insects. If the party bring her evidence of the work of the Grue and the dead larvae she will wish to go and deal with the Grue, and seeks the parties help to do so.
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs26 \uc0\u8232 She will also offer to sell her potions at 3d6 x 15 g.p. each and will take orders, although brewing them takes 2d4 days per potion.
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\b\fs26 \cf0 Harmful
\f1\b0\fs24 \

\f0\fs26 She\'92ll take umbrage at a party that wantonly attack her flock and will do everything she can to destroy them. She\'92ll also offer rewards to the goblins and bargain with the Fungal King to have them capture or kill the party. 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\b\fs26 \cf0 Disdainful
\f1\b0\fs24 \

\f0\fs26 The Banshaer will not offer up any advice or claim to know much about the level at all, but will offer potions for sale, at 3d6 x 20 g.p. She won\'92t offer to make further potions for them, believing the party will be killed before they can come to collect them. \'a0
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\b\fs26 \cf0 46. Ancient Throne Room (remove corridor 46) : teleporter
\f1\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\i\fs26 \cf0 A large bare chamber that is comparatively dry and debris free, this chamber displays only small signs of the collapse of the other areas locally. In the centre of the room is a raised stone platform, quite plain except for linked chain motifs chiselled into the rock. On top of the platform is a large and important looking stone chair. 
\f1\i0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\fs26 \cf0 The chair radiates magic, and if sat on properly it teleports the individual to an identical chair in Tomb Of Judder, a hidden section on this level. This is a one way teleport. The teleport works only when the target chair is empty, but functions any number of times.}